A message that was doing the rounds on Android devices through WhatsApp has made its way to iPhones, where it is causing problems. Among WhatsApp users on Android, the message would cause WhatsApp to hang if you open it. You then had to close and relaunch WhatsApp. In iOS Messages, however, the same text causes the app to hang immediately, AppleInsider reported. Closing and relaunching the app does not appear to resolve the issue. The bug affects iPhones and iPads running iOS 11.3 and the beta releases of iOS 11.4. Workarounds users are currently using include: 